laboratory_examinations.findings: Mild bibasilar atelectasis; no large pleural effusion or pericardial effusion; liver shows homogenous attenuation, no focal lesions; pancreatic duct normal; spleen normal; normal adrenal glands; kidneys normal size with no lesions; moderate soft tissue stranding about the appendix, fluid filled and dilated up to 8 mm, mucosal wall hyperemia; no appendicolith; no free fluid in pelvis; small anterior fibroid in uterus; bilateral adnexal cystic structures may reflect a corpus luteum.
